[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=d1498e8d5a7&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=d1498e8d5a7&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-12831&quot; title=&quot;DeleteShardCmd doesn&amp;#39;t remove all its data from Zookeeper&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-12831&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-12831&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Clean up ZK nodes after shard deletion is invoked (#3314)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Delete left over znodes on zookeeper that aren&apos;t removed after a delete shard command is issued. In DeleteShardCmd, use the zk client to issue a recursive delete from the specified root and its children (including that root).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
